28/05/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Some 3,750 domestic and foreign observers are expected to monitor the 5 July parliamentary elections, local civil association Most announced on Friday (26 May). 
According to the statement, the ODIHR will deploy about 250 monitors; the rest will be representatives of Macedonian organisations.
Also Friday, the results of a new survey were released, indicating broad pessimism about efforts to fight corruption. 
According to the poll by the Institute for Sociologist and Political-Legal Studies, around 65 per cent of respondents were sceptical about rooting out of corruption in the country. 
The customs sector was considered most corrupt, followed by the courts and political parties. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 27/05/06; A1 TV - 26/05/06)
